clause.p:
In practice, chemical measurements require the realization, across all types of chemical entities, of derived units involving amount of substance that are relevant to practical chemical measurement, such as the amount of substance concentration (mol/m3









), the amount of substance content (mol/kg










) or the amount of substance fraction (mol/mol). This may be done by a variety of primary methods of measurement . The present definition of the mole allows the number of entities N in a sample to be determined to the same accuracy as the amount of substance n in the sample because, from , N=nNA and NA has an exact numerical value.
